caption: I had take out here and the customer service is amazing. They took the time to call me as soon as they received my online order to inform me that the mango salad was out. On top of that the staff went above and beyond to make sure that I had something else, taking the time to offer me a plethora of options. And to top it all off the food was really good!!

I had the Pad Thai and Green Curry.  The Pad Thai was too sweet for me.  The Green Curry was good; would be better with brown rice.  Good service.  I look forward to trying something else the next time I eat here.
Our absolute favorite!  Talay Thai has the best happy hour in DC and the staff could not be kinder. Super highly recommend stopping in for a drink and the spring rolls!
Best Thai around. Decent prices. Tom Ka, drunken noodles and red curry delight are all top notch.
Exceptional place to grab something when in a hurry. The customer service is prompt, rates are fair, excellent mood. I highly recommend this place

Not sure why this place has anything below a 4.5. Luckily my roommate doesn’t look at reviews and took us here on Friday. I got the red curry with duck and it was amazing especially for the price. 10/10 recommend.
Awesome . Little in the wall near the capital building. Worth every reasonable dollar that they charge

Know the food before you come into the restaurant, or you’ll get lost in the menu. Great appetizers, make sure to try the Thai tea, it’s sort of like the Thai version of horchata, if you’re familiar with Mexican food.

Should have left a review years ago. My friend turned me onto this place a few years back and it has become my go to carry out in the Navy Yard/se/Sw area ever since The customer service and food is always amazing. Never feel shorted by portions or seasoning. The staff is very kind as are the happy hour pours 😬. I like that this place is a Thai restaurant the most. They don’t offer five other types of Cuisine as many other restaurants offer I the area (positive for quality here). Five stars for their efforts with dine-in service during Covid and positive attitude.

The Red Curry is sooo good!  The heat and the flavor is on point! My husband had Mussaman Curry and he thought is was very good. He asked for hot was and the heat was just right and not very hot. The Thai iced tea was delicious and worth a try! The drunken noodles with beef had lots of flavor. The Pad Thai was amazing and the pineapple fried rice with chicken was a winner as well. Our table of 5 received really good service and we are leaving full and glad we came!!! This definitely a place to try!

This restaurant is my preferred one. I go to a lot of restaurants but to this restaurant I  constantly return again and again. The crew is very chummy and the cuisine they serve is so good. I would always prefer to have a good meal in this place. I recommend this place with pleasure.
High quality food made by a good staff. Convenient for those working on the Hill.
Excellent food and very clean.
The best
Awesome food!

Consistently good. The red curry delight with tofu is delicious, and their tom ka soup is honestly some of the best I've ever had. We've tried a lot of Thai places in the area before finding this spot. We won't go anywhere else now!
Close to work, food was quick and tasty! Appetizers was good, but the shrimp was not what expected. Still yummy!!
The meals and service were above our expectations. I surely loved the vibes of this place. Great restaurant to take my family out for lunch.

We enjoy hanging out. Last night we came to this delicious place which friends recommended to us. We had a lovely evening there with excellent meal and a courteous stuff and an impressive chief cook. We  added this venue in our list  and we shall surely return soon. We warmly recommend.
The red curry was delicious! Very quiet and clean little restaurant.
First visit, had the drunken noodles with chicken (one of my benchmarks for Thai food). Very good indeed. Service was prompt and friendly. Will definitely be going back.
Good food, reasonable prices, and friendly staff.
It was delicious. Definitely worth a try. Also the Thai coffee is amazing.

Tonight was the first time I have dined at this restaurant. Technically I carried out. I had the shrimp pad Thai which cost a little over $17 and was a good portion. I thought the food was delicious, although very little spice. I have only had Pad Thai one other time, but I would recommend this dish.
Best spot to eat something when in a rush. Their customer service is speedy, prices are fair, fantastic character. Keep up the good work
Best restaurant near US Capitol building Closed on lunch break Big space for group travelers
Great Thai options for the area. I loved my pad Thai.

Really nothing special about this place. We ordered "Thai salad" and it was very much disappointing. A lot of lettuce with hard to eat broccoli and cauliflower. The main dish (spicy eggplant with tofu) was just ok.
Very good Thai and excellent service.  After a day of meetings on the Hill, who couldn't use a little spicy curry!

Great service and pretty standard Thai food.  I had the massaman curry and it tasted like it should.  The only complaint I had was one of the potatoes in the curry was still a little frozen/cold in the center.  Not a huge deal but still a little odd.

I go to this unique restaurant from time to time because I like the ambiance that is outline this place. The personel is exceptionally loyal and professional. The service is extraordinarily fast. Not to mention, the food they cook is perfect. I came more than once and I was always delighted. The price is reasobable. I highly suggest this restaurant to all my friends.

Talay has one of the best happy hours here by the Hill, and is always a good time to visit with coworkers. On top of their good pricing and friendly staff, their food is also above satisfactory. It wasn't the best Panang Curry I've ever had, but it was reasonably priced and hit the spot. Talay is a great place to spend a few hours after work with your friends. I look forward to visiting again.

Definitely my last time going, I wanted basil fried rice and got shrimp fried rice with egg I dont eat eggs, I call back and she stated I would have to walk back to exchange the rice, well my lunch is over now! 15.35 for 5 shrimp and some rice, who's the fool here! not no more.. last time.. dont go, unless you like expensive rice!
Good food. May want to bring ear plugs as it is noisy loud.
The food was amazing. When we are back in DC this will be a place we come back to.
The food is constantly well prepared and delightful, cashiers hands over excellent customer service. I liked the cleanliness and ambience. Will visit here again.
Great food.
Good food, good prices and fast service.  A great stop!
Seafood could be better but good overall

I was surprised by the lunch sticker prices. The Pad Thai was good but the portion was hardly enough to satisfy my appetite at $15.95. As such, I ordered chicken herb soup, at the recommendation of the waitress, to complete my lunch but it tasted old and was thrown in the garbage. Perhaps, it was because I ordered carryout that it tasted foul. But, should that matter? I was really disappointed to throw my money down the drain like that; the soup was $4.95.  I did like the Thai tea. It is very sweet and tasty. If you order it, put lots of ice in it or get it without ice and chill in the freezer before drinking. Like I said, I enjoyed the entree but not enough to give them a thumbs up.
The service is fast and curtious. The chicken pad thai that I had was delicious and was a reasonable cost. The restaurant is conveniently located near the capital building.
Good food. Great happy hour! Will def return!
Good food
The food was very good.  This place is about a block from the Capital South metro station.  I wished I knew about it before.
We have a small group meeting here & had good service & good food. They are vegetarian-friendly. Parking is on the street.
Yummy Thai food. Sat outside overlooking the Capitol South area 1 block from the Metro station. Good service. Good food!
Good lunch

Typical Thai restaurant, Nothing special, but big dishes for good prices. You can order different types of food and mix it with chicken or shrimps. You can order ice tea or soda and it would be refill if you want for free. Here it’s healthier food than in more American cafes. There are spicy dishes, but you can ask to make not spicy. The waitresses are so nice.
Great cashew chicken & happy hour, good Pad peanut sauce chicken, sweet mai tai. Plenty of food. Very good noodle dish also.

I love Thai food and enjoy it all over the country. This was absolutely delicious. The Panang Chicken (with extra vegetables added) was gluten free and spiced perfectly. The Sweet and sour chicken was a hit with my husband.  Definitely will be back!!

The first night a friend and I went to Talay Thai was an interesting experience. Both of us were staying in DC for work for around two months, and a long way from home, wanted something easy but good. Curries for the friend, and Tom Yum for myself. By the fourth time, they knew our drinks order off by heart.  The staff were always incredibly friendly, welcoming, prompt, and above all, cook really damn good food. There was not a night where said friend and I went to Talay Thai and left disappointed. They were always a spot of warmth, familiarity, friendliness and comfort food on what were often long, cold DC nights. I've not left a Google review before, but this one is worth making an exception for. They're just a thai restaurant--a normal, real thai restaurant with real people cooking good thai food for a real fair price, and for what they are, and for what they meant to two travellers, they are worth a clear five stars.
We've become regulars! The food here is delicious every time & the customer service we receive  is great. Their to-go orders are just as delicious as well
Popped in on a whim. Superb.
(Translated by Google) Delicious food, friendly atmosphere  (Original) อาหารอร่อย บรรยากาศเป็นกันเอง
good
Convenient place
Eat the curry puffs!!
Good but plates are small

I give this place 1 star just for being a restaurant. I asked to purchase a cup of ice to go along with my lunch and they acted like I was asking for something they don't sell. Then,  they went to get the manager who said" we don't sell that kind of thing here". What she should've said was, she didn't want to give it to me. Standing from my side of the bar I could see plastic cups and ice. I would never recommend this place to anyone. I would give zero stars if I could. People are losing the simplicity of being a human. Everything isn't about money, it's about respect and having a good heart. I should've left a tip just to be sarcastic.  #Whatgoesaroundcomesaround
Good tastey fresh food!
Interesting food and decent service
(Translated by Google) Delicious food, the owner is very kind 👍👍👍  (Original) อาหารอร่อย เจ้าของร้านใจดีมากค่ะ 👍👍👍
Nice quiet hidden gem with outstanding Panang Chicken Curry.
Best Thai food in the area but wow expensive paid 17 bucks for order of beef fried rice actually might have been more they get me all the time because the cooking is good.
This is the best Pad Thai that has ever been made. I'm no kidding. It is the best.

Food was great! Ordered over the phone and it was ready 10 minutes later. They were fast and very nice. We got the chicken pad thai and beef pad see-yew. Both were fantastic! Great portions and prices.
Disappointing. Extremely small portions for the price. Ambiguous quality – genuinely gave me the impression it had been sitting in a pot for hours. Will not order again.
Love it
Food was pretty good and the service was great too. They can probably do some work on the ambiance.
Delicious chicken pad thai!
Great service
Consistently great Thai food that's been a staple of Capitol Hill for many years.
Excelent Pad Thai!

Went there with my family of 4 during visit to Washington DC in July 2017.  Ordered 4 dishes and one appetizer. While ordering, the waitress did not say the food I ordered would be too much. They made a bigger sale for themselves, although we had to waste half the food (we could not take the food back to our hotel). I did not like this behaviour at all. Dishes were OK. I will not go back again.
Decent Thai food, standard fare.

I was in the area on a vacation trip and a bunch of other matters. I settled for Talay Thai because the southwestern place next door had an hour-long wait for a table. Talay Thai, in contrast, was rather quiet with only a few tables occupied. I ordered the Pad Thai with chicken. That's the one thing common to all Thai restaurants, so it should be a reasonable choice. My impression of this dish is it's only about average, not outstanding, although the portion size is on the large side and satisfying. It's priced on the high side though. Aside from that, the service was good and the dining area and restroom seemed clean enough. Overall however, it's an average experience and I am sure you could do better in DC.
(Translated by Google) It's okay for the money in the area. but has flaws.  (Original) Ist okay für das Geld in der Gegend. Hat aber Mängel.
Yummy food
Awesome food, great service. This place is great.
Solid American Thai. Fresh ingredients and friedly service. Don't be afraid that it is not popular. It's not personal. People in DC don't seem to into Thai.
Just ok. Nothing makes me want to go back again.
Great food! The panang curry was some of the best I have ever had! The eggplant tofu was also superb. Nice, quiet, oasis away from the chaos of the Mall. Interesting decor and wood paneling.
(Translated by Google) Very tasty, Thai flavor. The shop owner is lovely. Very good service.  (Original) อร่อยมากรสชาติไทยๆเจ้าของร้านน่ารักบริการดีมากกก
Food is so so.....service is ok.

caption: more like 2 and 1/2 stars.  nice staff--homey, welcoming atmosphere.  full bar (kind of--limited selection).  food is only passable.  I had a tom yum with shrimp that was very heavy on the fish sauce.
The pad see ew was probably the worst I've ever had. No flavor, way too much oil. Just not good. Delivery was fast but unfortunately matched with underwhelming food.
Nice little place not far from the Capitol South Metro stop. Ordered the Pad See Ew and it wasn't very flavorful. Needed to ask for the spice rack. The staff was very friendly.
The food was not very good the service was poor I had to send the  food back. I will not return for more. And they have the nerve to be overpriced.
The food literally smelled like vomit in a cup. It was inedible. Very overpriced. Waste of money
Ordered food online. 2 hours later, no delivery. No apologies, no follow-up. Definitely not worth ordering, terrible service and no food!
The food here lacks any flavor other than spicy. The service was decent.
Our go-to Thai place on the Hill. Friendly, convenient, great menu.

Went there after a long day of walk around the mall. Very nice Thai food, much better than what we had two days ago in another Thai restaurant. Pleasant seating and super friendly staff. The "ginger lover" dish that the waiter recommended was my favorite.
